  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Administrative Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>We are seeking a responsible and detail-oriented Administrative Assistant to support daily pharmacy and office operations. This role involves administrative coordination, order processing, invoicing support, logistics coordination, and general office duties.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Manage prescription documentation by accurately filing and maintaining records to ensure compliance and easy retrieval</li><li>Process online and retail orders and coordinate timely third-party deliveries to meet customer expectations</li><li>Pack local and international shipments accurately and ensure on-time dispatch to maintain service quality</li><li>Assist with invoicing, billing, and daily sales closing to support financial accuracy and reporting</li><li>Receive incoming goods and perform basic stock tracking and expiry date checks to maintain inventory accuracy</li><li>Coordinate communications and logistics with clinics, couriers, suppliers, and internal teams to facilitate smooth operations</li><li>Prepare brochures, samples, and materials for clinics or events to support marketing and outreach efforts</li><li>Answer phone calls, manage incoming mail, and maintain office tidiness to ensure an organized work environment</li><li>Perform other administrative and support duties as assigned to contribute to overall office efficiency</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum GCE 'O' Levels or equivalent (preferred but not mandatory)</li><li>At least 1 year of administrative or office support experience preferred</li><li>Basic computer skills including email, spreadsheets, and online systems</li><li>Experience in pharmacy, healthcare, logistics, retail, or e-commerce is an advantage</li><li>Strong organisational skills demonstrated by managing multiple tasks and meeting deadlines</li><li>Effective communication skills for interacting with external parties and internal teams</li><li>Ability to work independently and collaboratively within a team</li><li>Personal attributes including reliability, punctuality, responsibility, willingness to learn, initiative, calmness, professionalism, and team orientation</li></ul>",
